iption\n    52→\n    53→Detailed description of what needs to be done.\n    54→\n    55→## Context\n    56→\n    57→- Links to documentation\n    58→- Related files\n    59→- Design (Figma)\n    60→- Architecture decisions\n    61→\n    62→## Constraints\n    63→\n    64→- Do not touch X\n    65→- Use Y pattern\n    66→- Backward compatibility requirements\n    67→\n    68→## Acceptance Criteria\n    69→\n    70→- [ ] Criterion 1\n    71→- [ ] Criterion 2\n    72→- [ ] Criterion 3\n    73→\n    74→## Artifacts\n    75→\n    76→- Source code: src/features/profile/\n    77→- Tests: src/test/features/profile/\n    78→\n    79→## Team Specification\n    80→\n    81→| Role | Agent |\n    82→|------|-------|\n    83→| Developer | senior-android-developer |\n    84→| Reviewer | android-code-reviewer |\n    85→| QA | qa-expert |\n    86→\n    87→## Status: Ready for dev\n    88→## Updated: 2026-03-05 10:00:00\n    89→```\n    90→\n    91→### Field Definitions\n    92→\n    93→| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n    94→|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n    95→| id | string | Yes | Unique task identifier (e.g., CORE-001) |\n    96→| title | string | Yes | Short task title |\n    97→| type | enum | Yes | One of: feature, bug, refactor, research, docs |\n    98→| priority | number | Yes | 1-4 (1=Critical, 2=High, 3=Medium, 4=Low) |\n    99→| assignee | string | No | Agent assigned to the task |\n   100→| depends_on | array | No | List of task IDs that block this task |\n   101→| blocks | array | No | List of task IDs that this task blocks |\n   102→| created_at | datetime | Yes | ISO 8601 timestamp |\n   103→| updated_at | datetime | Yes | ISO 8601 timestamp |\n   104→| status | string | Yes | Current task status |\n   105→| attempt | number | No | Number of execution attempts (default: 0) |\n   106→\n   107→> Important: This file is always guaranteed to exist. If it's not there - require the user to create it.\n   108→\n   109→---\n   110→\n   111→## Task Status\n   112→\n   113→Task status shows progress of each performer:\n   114→\n   115→### Core Statuses\n   116→\n   117→| Status | Description |\n   118→|--------|-------------|\n   119→| `Ready for dev` | Task waiting for developer to pick it up |\n   120→| `Dev in progress` | Developer has picked up the task |\n   121→| `Ready for review` | Developer completed work, waiting for code review |\n   122→| `Review in progress` | Code reviewer has picked up the task |\n   123→| `Ready for QA review` | Code reviewer completed, waiting for QA |\n   124→| `QA review in progress` | QA has picked up the task |\n   125→| `Verified` | Work on task is completed |\n   126→| `Blocked` | Task is blocked by dependencies or external factors |\n   127→\n   128→### Priority Levels\n   129→\n   130→| Priority | Name | SLA | Description |\n   131→|----------|------|-----|-------------|\n   132→| 1 | Critical | Today | Blocking production or critical path |\n   133→| 2 | High | This week | Important feature or significant bug |\n   134→| 3 | Medium | This sprint | Regular feature or improvement |\n   135→| 4 | Low | When possible | Nice-to-have or minor improvement |\n   136→\n   137→### Timestamp\n   138→> Important: Always put date and time next to task status when setting it\n   139→\n   140→Always specify task completion time strictly in format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss (for example, 2026-02-25 10:43:00).\n   141→Don't add extra words or explanations before the date.\n   142→\n   143→**Examples:**\n   144→- `Ready for dev` - 2026-02-11 10:43:00\n   145→- `Verified` - 2025-12-24 18:15:43\n   146→\n   147→### Status Workflow\n   148→\n   149→```mermaid\n   150→flowchart TD\n   151→\n   152→A[Ready for Dev]\n   153→B[Dev in Progress]\n   154→C[Ready for Review]\n   155→D[Review in Progress]\n   156→E[Ready for QA Review]\n   157→F[QA Review in Progress]\n   158→G[Verified]\n   159→H[Blocked]\n   160→\n   161→A --> B\n   162→B --> C\n   163→C --> D\n   164→D --> E\n   165→E --> F\n   166→F --> G\n   167→\n   168→%% Rework loops\n   169→C -- changes requested --> A\n   170→F -- bugs found --> A\n   171→\n   172→%% Blocked state\n   173→A -- has unmet dependencies --> H\n   174→B -- external blocker --> H\n   175→H -- dependencies resolved --> A\n   176→H -- blocker removed --> B\n   177→```\n   178→\n   179→### Blocked Status\n   180→\n   181→Task enters `Blocked` status when:\n   182→1. `depends_on` contains a task ID that is not `Verified`\n   183→2. External blocker exists (no API access, waiting for response, etc.)\n   184→\n   185→Task exits `Blocked` status when:\n   186→1. All tasks in `depends_on` are `Verified`\n   187→2. External blocker is removed manually via `/unblock_task`\n   188→\n   189→---\n   190→\n   191→## Dependencies\n   192→\n   193→### depends_on\n   194→\n   195→Specifies tasks that must complete before this task can start.\n   196→\n   197→```yaml\n   198→depends_on:\n   199→  - \"CORE-001\"\n   200→  - \"CORE-002\"\n   201→```\n   202→\n   203→**Rules:**\n   204→- Task cannot transition from `Ready for dev` to `Dev in progress` if any dependency is not `Verified`\n   205→- If dependencies are not met, task goes to `Blocked` status\n   206→- Circular dependencies are not allowed\n   207→\n   208→### blocks\n   209→\n   210→Specifies tasks that are waiting for this task to complete.\n   211→\n   212→```yaml\n   213→blocks:\n   214→  - \"CORE-005\"\n   215→  - \"CORE-006\"\n   216→```\n   217→\n   218→**Rules:**\n   219→- Automatically populated when another task has this task in its `depends_on`\n   220→- Used for impact analysis when blocking a task\n   221→\n   222→### Dependency Validation\n   223→\n   224→Before starting work on a task:\n   225→1. Check all tasks in `depends_on`\n   226→2. If any task is not `Verified`:\n   227→   - Set status to `Blocked`\n   228→   - Record blocker reason in task\n   229→3. If all dependencies are `Verified`:\n   230→   - Allow task to proceed\n   231→\n   232→---\n   233→\n   234→## Task History (Optional)\n   235→\n   236→File `task_history.md` tracks all status changes:\n   237→\n   238→```markdown\n   239→## History\n   240→\n   241→| Date | Status | Actor | Comment |\n   242→|------|--------|-------|---------|\n   243→| 2026-03-05 10:00 | Ready for dev | User | Task created |\n   244→| 2026-03-05 10:30 | Dev in progress | senior-android-developer | Started development |\n   245→| 2026-03-05 14:00 | Ready for review | senior-android-developer | Implementation complete |\n   246→| 2026-03-05 14:30 | Blocked | android-code-reviewer | Waiting for API docs |\n   247→| 2026-03-05 15:00 | Ready for review | User | Blocker removed |\n   248→```\n   249→\n   250→---\n   251→\n   252→## For Performers\n   253→\n   254→### Main Agent\n   255→Monitors statuses and calls corresponding performers.\n   256→- `Ready for dev` - calls `android-developer` agent (after checking dependencies)\n   257→- `Ready for review` - calls `android-code-reviewer` agent\n   258→- `Ready for QA review` - calls `qa-expert` agent\n   259→- `Verified` - work finished. Forming response to user\n   260→- `Blocked` - notify user about blocker\n   261→\n   262→**Constraints:**\n   263→- Main agent is prohibited from setting statuses independently. It can only monitor them and call corresponding agents.\n   264→- Prohibited from changing task content\n   265→- Prohibited from moving task to other directories\n   266→- Must check `depends_on` before allowing task to start\n   267→\n   268→### android-developer\n   269→Only monitors statuses related to development.\n   270→If status:\n   271→- `Ready for dev` - Sets new status - `Dev in progress`, because task was picked up.\n   272→- `Dev in progress` - After completing work, changes to `Ready for review`\n   273→- `Blocked` (if was in progress) - Record blocker, notify main agent\n   274→\n   275→**Requirements:**\n   276→- Prohibited from changing others' statuses.\n   277→- Flow strictly `Ready for dev` -> Start work -> Set `Dev in progress` -> Finish work -> Set status `Ready for review`\n   278→\n   279→### android-code-reviewer\n   280→Only monitors statuses related to code review.\n   281→If status:\n   282→- `Ready for review` - Sets new status - `Review in Progress`, because task was picked up.\n   283→- `Review in Progress`\n   284→  - After completing work, if no comments, changes to `Ready for QA Review`\n   285→  - After completing work, if there are comments, sets status `Ready for dev`\n   286→\n   287→**Requirements:**\n   288→- Prohibited from changing others' statuses.\n   289→- Flow strictly `Ready for review` -> Start work -> Set `Review in Progress` -> Finish work -> `Ready for dev` OR `Ready for QA Review`\n   290→\n   291→### qa-expert\n   292→Only monitors statuses related to QA review.\n   293→If status:\n   294→- `Ready for QA Review` - Sets new status - `QA Review in Progress`, because task was picked up.\n   295→- `QA Review in Progress`\n   296→    - After completing work, if no comments, changes to `Verified`\n   297→    - After completing work, if there are comments, sets status `Ready for dev`\n   298→\n   299→**Requirements:**\n   300→- Prohibited from changing others' statuses.\n   301→- Flow strictly `Ready for QA Review` -> Start work -> Set `QA Review in Progress` -> Finish work -> `Ready for dev` OR `Verified`\n   302→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n",
